The paper discusses the application of graphical models and message passing algorithms to solve compressed sensing problems, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The focus is on image reconstruction, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the derivation of fast algorithms, which is a topic of interest in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
